    "biography": "<p>Fanatically religious, nomadic people who wander steppes and desert regions, living in tents.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Mounted: </strong>On warhorses.</li>\n<li><strong>Arms: </strong>50% of group have: leather armour, shield, lance; 25% have: leather armour, shield, shortbow, sword; 25% have: chainmail, shield, lance.</li>\n<li><strong>Camps:</strong> Groups commonly combine and live in a camp or tribe of up to 300 dervishes, plus women, children, and animals. 25% chance of a wood or brick enclosure.</li>\n<li><strong>Camp leaders: </strong>Led by 10th level cleric.</li>\n<li><strong>Intolerant:</strong> Of other religious views.</li>\n<li><strong>Holy war:</strong> Occasionally wage war against other religious factions. Will slay people of different faith, or take them prisoner. Prisoners must convert; otherwise killed or used as slaves. Characters of Lawful alignment may be asked to join the holy war. Dervishes are highly suspicious of those who refuse (without good reason).</li>\n</ul>"
  },
